The paper focuses on a methodology for performing systematic reviews in the sub-area of Software Engineering, which suggests that cs.SE is the most likely category. The methodology also involves the use of ontology-learning techniques and semantic technologies, which are commonly associated with cs.AI and cs.CL. The paper also mentions the use of automatic classification of primary studies, which falls under the scope of cs.IR and cs.LG.
